queue-it.com
Description of Queue-it-queueitcom__________qitcom001 set by Queue-it
Cookie name:
Queue-it-queueitcom__________qitcom001
Purpose:
This cookie contains the Queue-it Visitor ID and language selection for a specific Waiting Room, ensuring that the Waiting Room page is displayed in the correct language for the given customerId. It also provides fault tolerance; for example, if the end user closes their browser and later reopens it to check their progress in the Waiting Room, this cookie helps maintain their session.
Policy:
Link to policy (queue-it.com)
Open policy for Queue-it in new window
Removed after:
When browser is closed
Domain:
queueitcom.queue-it.net
Description of QueueITAccepted-SDFrts345E-V3_qitcom001 set by Queue-it
Cookie name:
QueueITAccepted-SDFrts345E-V3_qitcom001
Purpose:
This cookie is set by the Connector when the end user visits the Customer’s Protected URLs (server side and JavaScript integrations) after having successfully acquired a Connector Token. It contains details used to verify if an end user has a valid session for a given Waiting Room (eventId) and can stay on the Protected URL
Policy:
Link to policy (queue-it.com)
Open policy for Queue-it in new window
Removed after:
1 hour, 21 minutes
Domain:
queue-it.com
Description of queueitsoftblock_{queueId} set by Queue-it
Cookie name:
queueitsoftblock_{queueId}
Purpose:
This cookie contains a hash of the CAPTCHA generated by QueueFront in case that an end-user was softblocked and successfully solved the challenge.
Policy:
Link to policy (queue-it.com)
Open policy for Queue-it in new window
Removed after:
1 day
Domain:
queue-it.net
Description of Queue-it-token set by Queue-it
Cookie name:
Queue-it-token
Purpose:
This cookie contains details used by the QueueFront server to verify if an end user has already been allocated a Connector Token (queueittoken url parameter) as a fallback option in case the latest Connector Token query string parameter is lost from the URL redirect when the end user attempts to access the Protected URL
Policy:
Link to policy (queue-it.com)
Open policy for Queue-it in new window
Removed after:
3 minutes
Domain:
queue-it.net
Description of Queue-it-{customerId}________{eventId} set by Queue-it
Cookie name:
Queue-it-{customerId}________{eventId}
Purpose:
This cookie contains the Queue-it Visitor ID and language selection for a specific Waiting Room to display the Waiting Room page in the correct language and for the given customerId. This cookie is also used for fault tolerance in a similar manner to the Queue-it Visual Waiting Room Backup Cookie
Policy:
Link to policy (queue-it.com)
Open policy for Queue-it in new window
Removed after:
1 day
Domain:
queue-it.net
Description of Queue-it-{queueId} set by Queue-it
Cookie name:
Queue-it-{queueId}
Purpose:
This cookie contains data about the user’s queueId. This cookie is used for the following purposes:
Fault tolerance, for example, if the end user closes their browser and later reopens their browser to check their progress in the Waiting Room
To carry a set of Waiting Room specific parameters
Policy:
Link to policy (queue-it.com)
Open policy for Queue-it in new window
Removed after:
1 hour
Domain:
queue-it.net
